org.slf4j.impl

Class CasDelegatingLogger

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.slf4j.helpers.MarkerIgnoringBase
      • org.slf4j.impl.CasDelegatingLogger
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, org.slf4j.Logger

    public final class CasDelegatingLogger
extends org.slf4j.helpers.MarkerIgnoringBase
implements Serializable
    The CAS logger wrapper, which uses a substitute logger to route the logs. This component only exists to intercept logging calls before they are sent to the logging engine (log4j, etc) and serves to manipulate logging messages if needed, such as removing sensitive ticket id from the log message.
    Since:
    4.1.0
    Author:
    Misagh Moayyed
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
